### 2. Unit of Work Interface

**File**: `{{ s.global.prefix }}/{{ feat.snake_name }}/use_cases/{{ uc.snake_name }}_uc/i_{{ uc.snake_name }}_uow.h`

Declare which entity operations the use case needs. Available macros (from `uow_macros.h`):

```cpp
// Granular macros:
DECLARE_UOW_ENTITY_GET(EntityName)                       // get by ids
DECLARE_UOW_ENTITY_GET_ALL(EntityName)                   // get all
DECLARE_UOW_ENTITY_CREATE(EntityName)                    // create with owner
DECLARE_UOW_ENTITY_CREATE_ORPHANS(EntityName)            // create without owner
DECLARE_UOW_ENTITY_UPDATE(EntityName)                    // update
DECLARE_UOW_ENTITY_REMOVE(EntityName)                    // remove
DECLARE_UOW_ENTITY_SNAPSHOT(EntityName)                  // snapshot + restore (for undo)
DECLARE_UOW_ENTITY_RELATIONSHIPS(EntityName, RelField)   // relationship get/set/count/range
DECLARE_UOW_ENTITY_GET_REL_FROM_OWNER(EntityName)        // get rel ids from owner
DECLARE_UOW_ENTITY_SET_REL_IN_OWNER(EntityName)          // set rel ids in owner

// Composite macros:
DECLARE_UOW_ENTITY_CRUD(EntityName)                      // all of the above
DECLARE_UOW_ORPHAN_ENTITY_CRUD(EntityName)               // CRUD without owner-based create
```

